*****************************************
Game Of Life Application
*****************************************

1. The application takes in put from input.txt file placed inside WebContent/files of the application.
2. The application writes the output of each run in output_<timestamp>.txt. The results can be verified 
   by analyzing the output.
   
   
******************************************
Technology stack
******************************************

1. The application uses JSF 2, Java 7 and Ant for build.

******************************************
Build and Deploy Instructions
******************************************

1. Please install Apache Tomcat 7 from https://tomcat.apache.org/download-70.cgi . (Default tomcat port - 8080)
2. Create environment property - CATALINA_HOME and set it to Tomcat root directory.
3. Apache ant (https://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi). (Default port - 8080)
4. Create environment property - ANT_HOME and set it to Ant root directory.
5. Append the following to Path variable - %CATALINA_HOME%\bin and %ANT_HOME%\bin.
6. Build the code using command - ant -f build.xml.
7. Copy the war file to %CATALINA_HOME%\webapps.
8. Restart the server. 

*******************************************
Application URL
*******************************************

1. http://localhost:<tomcat_port>/GameOfLifeWeb/faces/lifeBean.xhtml

*******************************************
Additional Features
*******************************************
1. The application has an option to open the file location where the output files are written. 
2. The user can view the input and output on a web page in form of grid. Alive cells are RED and dead ones are BLACK.
3. The user has an option to edit the value of a given cell in the web page itself.

********************************************
Constraint
********************************************

1. The application can open the output folder in Windows OS.
2. Application doesn't use AJAX.